## Instructions
1. Determine tx_type from: "transfer", "swap", "liquidity_add", "liquidity_remove", "stake", "unstake", "bridge", "mint", "burn", "approval", "contract_deploy", "governance_vote", "claim", "nft_trade", or "other".
2. Identify protocol_name by matching the to/from address or function signature to known Base protocols (e.g. Aerodrome, Uniswap, BaseSwap, Aave, Compound, OpenSea).
3. Assign protocol_category: "dex", "lending", "bridge", "nft_marketplace", "yield_aggregator", "governance", "stablecoin", "launchpad", "gaming", or "other".
4. Use the decoded input data, event logs, and address labels to make the most accurate classification.

## Null Rules
1. Return null for tx_type only if the transaction data is too ambiguous to classify; prefer "other" over null when some data exists.
2. Return null for protocol_name if no known protocol can be identified.
3. Return null for protocol_category if protocol_name is null.

## Output Format
JSON only:
{
  "tx_type": "string|null",
  "protocol_name": "string|null",
  "protocol_category": "string|null"
}
